news.title: IWG posts $752.1 million revenue in July-Sept 2021
news.para: The Swiss-based company, which has centres in more than 3,300 locations across 110 countries, said it has started to "assess the strategic and commercial rationale for separating the digital and technology assets into a separately identified and constituted business".

news.title: PNB Housing Finance's net profit dips 25% in Q2 FY22
news.para: The board of directors approved the issuance of secured and unsecured non-convertible debentures (NCDs) aggregating upto an amount of Rs 2,000 crore in one or more tranches, on private placement basis, PNB Housing said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Get fire NOC by November 30, or face sealing: Mohali civic body
news.para: The department said it had issued 644 NOCs in 2017 and issued 320 notices in 2018 and 98 in 2019. In 2020, the pandemic prevented checks but none of the violators had complied with the notices.

news.title: Godrej Properties posts net profit of Rs 35 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Godrej Properties' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 334.22 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 34 per cent from Rs 250.23 crore it registered in the similar quarter of last year.

news.title: Jharkhand government launches Svamitva Yojana for property mapping
news.para: Under the scheme, the state department of revenue, land records and registration will join hands with the Survey of India to create digital records of immovable properties belonging to residents of rural areas in the state.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body launches online portal for property tax payments
news.para: The portal was launched by MLA’s D Vedavyas Kamath, Dr Bharath Shetty, mayor Premananda Shetty and MCC commissioner Akshy Sridhar on Monday.

news.title: Nashik civic body approves 230 building proposals in October 2021
news.para: The total construction cost of these projects would be in the tune of at least Rs 100 crore — excluding the land cost — and are expected to add around 600 apartments in the next two to three years.

news.title: Now, 'tatkal' system for same-day registration of property in Goa
news.para: "We are launching the tatkal scheme for such instances where, after paying a special higher fee, a person can register the document on the same day itself,” Cabral said.

news.title: Nine years on, nine Mumbai families to get redevelopment flats on Nov 2
news.para: The order by Justice Gautam Patel came on a contempt petition filed by the society against K Mordani Builders over the delay. The original five-floor building with 10 flats was given to the builder in December 2012.

news.title: Greater Noida authority offers ready flats, applications from Nov 10
news.para: Under the scheme, some 113 independent houses ranging from 120 to 200 sqm are available along with 1,467 flats in built-up highrises of one, two and three bedrooms in different sectors. Online applications for the open-ended scheme will begin from November 10.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA cancels auction of flats by Union Bank of India
news.para: The authority also directed the bank to hand over the under-construction residential project ‘Sunrisers’ situated in C-Scheme area to RERA. The authority will ensure the project’s completion and handing over of the allotted flats to the buyers.

news.title: Gurugram: Homes delayed, Vatika India Next township buyers protest
news.para: At least 50 protesters marched from Sapphire Mall to Vatika City Centre under the banner of Senior Citizen Association, holding placards and shouting slogans against the developer.

news.title: Star Cement's profit down 22.79% to Rs 46.53 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Company's revenue from operations was at Rs 406.56 crore, up 1.16 per cent, during the period under review as against Rs 401.89 crore of the corresponding quarter, Star Cement in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Income tax department attaches Ajoy Mehta's south Mumbai flat
news.para: The I-T department probe found that the seller, Anamitra Properties Pvt Ltd, was a shell company floated by Bhosale to ‘hold’ the ‘benami asset’ (the flat), which he subsequently sold to ‘old acquaintance’ Mehta, the sources added.

news.title: Greater Noida: Supertech Ecovillage 1 fined for violating waste rules twice
news.para: ​In August too, a fine of Rs 2 lakh was levied on Ecovillage for violating solid waste management rules. Legal action will be initiated if the housing society fails to deposit the fine within three working days, officials said.
